The ELOs, Europol officers, analysts, and other experts, provide fast, effective, multilingual  service 24 hours a day.
Europol will increase its staff to 485 by the end of 2004.
Management and control stop at borders  and are actively establishing cooperative networks with accession states.
Europol has improved its international law-enforcement cooperation by negotiating bilateral operational, strategic agreements with other States and international organisations as follows : Colombia, Eurojust, European Central Bank, European Monitoring Centre on Drugs and Drug Addiction, Iceland, Interpol, Norway, Romania, Russia, United States of America and World Customs Organisation.
Fact sheet on Europol
Jan. "04"-EN
Europol answers to the Council of Ministers for Justice and Home Affairs.
JHA's responsibilities include guidance and control of Europol.
It appoints the Director and Deputy Directors and approves the budget.
The Council of Ministers contains representatives from all Member States, and requires uimous decisions to help ensure democratic control of Europol.
The Europol Management Board comprises one representative from each Member State, and has the task of supervising organisation activities.
Europol is the EU Union law-enforcement organisation that handles criminal intelligence.
Europol seeks to improve relations between the competent authorities of the Member States to prevent/combat international organized crime.
Europol's mission is to make a significant contribution to the European Union's law-enforcement action against organized crime, in particular criminal organizations.
The Joint Supervisory Body, comprising two data protection experts from each Member State, monitors personal data held by Europol.
